text.tspan: These playsheets incorporate graphical work from:
- Classic Mac OS, designed predominantly by Susan Kare (1982-1986)
including Giles Booth's reworking of the Chicago and Geneva fonts (2017)
- the following classic Mac OS software:
Black Night terminal emulator by Christopher Swan (1995-1997),
HyperCard Art Bits (1987-1998), Jurassic Park - Expanded Book (1991)
- NetRunner symbols font by Michael W. Delaney (2014)
- Plans of the Hanging Gardens of Basingstoke, by Michael Paul Lewis (2025)
- Photo of the interior of the Priroda module, Mir Space Station (1998)
Structural formulae were created using ChemDraw 2.1.3 (1989)
